#Approach:

Reverse Words in a String – Reverse Entire String + Reverse Each Word

Is problem me hume words ka order reverse karna hai, lekin characters ka order correct rehna chahiye.

Sabse pehle poori string ko reverse kar dete hain.
Isse words ka order reverse ho jata hai, lekin har word bhi reverse ho jata hai.

Ab reversed string me traverse karte hain aur har word ko alag nikaalte hain.
Har word ko dobara reverse kar dete hain taki word sahi ho jaye.

Agar word empty nahi hai, to usse result me add kar dete hain.
Aur ensure karte hain ki words ke beech sirf ek hi space aaye.

Is approach se:
extra spaces handle ho jaate hain,
leading aur trailing spaces remove ho jaate hain,
aur words correct order me reverse ho jaate hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String reverseWords(String s) {

        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        StringBuilder orignal = new StringBuilder(s);

        orignal.reverse();
        int n = orignal.length();
        
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            StringBuilder word = new StringBuilder();
            while(i < n && orignal.charAt(i) != ' '){
                word.append(orignal.charAt(i));
                i++;
            }

            word.reverse();

            if(word.length() > 0){
                if(result.length() > 0){
                    result.append(" ");
                }
                result.append(word);
            }
        }
        return result.toString();
        
    }
}
